<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880909-0023 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Citicorp </HL><SO> </SO><CO> CCI GE </CO><TEXT>   Kidder, Peabody andamp; Co., New York, signed a five-year agreement to install Quotron Systems Inc.'s Quotron 1000 branch office systems in Kidder's 75 brokerage offices in the U.S., the companies said. Financial terms weren't disclosed.    The accord represents one of several brokerage accounts recently signed by Los Angeles-based Quotron, a unit of Citicorp, New York, that provides financial information services. Kidder is a unit of General Electric Co., Fairfield, Conn.    Quotron already provides services to the investment banking and brokerage concern's offices in London, Paris, Geneva, Zurich, Osaka, Tokyo and Hong Kong, and its domestic trading operations. </TEXT></DOC>